commentBody:
@Mike 

His Caraway project is always green-lighted.

It'll take an early sage to catch a WORMHOLE working.

@Haim Wright 

Haim, glad you also were not totaled in that accident; that would have been the Final Solution!




Emus, too soon? Yeah, probably too soon.

@G 

I'm having my morning coffee and what I wouldn't give for a Paris-Brest right now! 
Thank you for introducing me to it. I love me any French pastry but wasn't familiar with this one. Yum!

@Steve L 

Except that it’s not new. I solved a Los Angeles Times crossword three or four years ago with the same gimmick. 

I don’t know whether Mr. Ayas borrowed the trick from that puzzle or came up with it independently. In either case, his puzzle was fun.

@Emma S I thought it was just me! So many great lines in that song.

Realizing it’s not a contest, but if I had $1,000,000 I’d buy Mr. Ayas a green dress (but not a real green dress; that’s cruel!). 

Thoroughly enjoyed this one!

@Treegarden 
Occupational Therapy!

DHubby is elderly (OMG OLDER than a certain Candidate!  Yikes!  Call the paramedics! Quick, put him in A Home!  Take away his keys!  Can he still sign his checks?...) anyway, trying to ease some stiff joints so he can perform his ADLs (Activities of Daily Living) and enjoy fishing, etc.  (He is my Geek Squad, jar-opener, account monitor, and fixer-upper....despite not being quite as spry as he was when I said, "I do."

@LordBottletop 

I worked forward from 1993, with occasional archive visits out of sequence. I just started on 2007, so I have a ways to go before I catch up to when I started solving regularly in 2020.

Grand total as of this morning: 7,550.

@DB 

Or maybe the constructor was trying very hard to produce a fun and interesting puzzle, rather than "show[ing] how clever he can be".

It's fine to not like a puzzle.  I am troubled, though, when motivations of the constructors and cluers are questioned.

@Joe 

I messed up that corner before gift of GAB came to me.
The only "gift" that would annoy me would be ESP, lol!

@Strudel Dad 

That's funny!  

Just a note, though.  For some reason you just can't click on the link.  You'll need to copy the entire link from "https:...." all the way to "...=abme,trie" to see it.

@Manuel Pagan 

I've been told the essence of recreation is when time passes without your noticing.  That's being intensely "in the moment".  

I love it when that happens to me.

@quarkcharm 

CANCY makes perfect sense. Here, I’ll use it in a sentence…

“I CANCY you don’t understand how the wormholes work in this puzzle. And, I think I CANCY this misunderstanding has led to some frustration that perhaps exceeds a level which an optional puzzle would warrant.”

@HeathieJ 

You exemplify the perfect attitude and temperament for crosswords.  

I am aspiring to that, and hope to be there soon.  I stumbled on that awful LENAPE/BELA day, but I'm trying to get re-centered.

@Jeremy 
Glad you enjoyed it! 

As a non-physicist, and a person who never had a physics course in HS or college,  I had a lot of problems with this one.

@Michael 
How did you solve the unchecked squares without grasping the theme? Connecting the first three words through the "wormholes" to the rest of the answer was the key to the whole puzzle.

Maybe I am misinterpreting your comment.

@Steven :
Ummm?

I can neither confirm or deny.

@Jeb Jones 

Several of my personal bests were on archived puzzles. I’ve since beaten most of them, but there may still be one or two old puzzles that are my personal records. 

If you look at your stats in a browser, you can see the date of each puzzle that was your fastest.

@HeathieJ 

In other words, "when all else fails, read the instructions".

Strange that in the old days, you didn't get a thousand word essay on the puzzle, or the ability to compare notes with hundreds of other solvers.  And yet, for some, it seems to do no good.

@Granville 

Funny.  The only one I ever remember is exultation of larks.

Hmm, I hope it's not a new policy that they open up comments only after midnight.  Because that would stink.

@Michael 

A fellow astronomy nerd!  Are you a member of, or would you consider being a member of, the Minnesota Astronomical Society?

Access to lots of very nice telescopes!
